race.comment: EDEN ROSE (3) resumes. She's yet to place in six starts but has contested stronger races, including an excellent fifth in the G1 Blue Diamond, albeit at $201. Finds a suitable race here and gets her chance to hit the board. Very wary of LYRICS 'N' SONG (7), an impeccably bred filly on debut for the Mark Walker yard. She's by Written Tycoon out of 14x G1 winner Melody Belle who looked good winning a recent jump out. Have to respect. MISS DECEIVER (8) worked home well on debut at Geelong to grab third and has each-way claims once more. SHOCAP (9) was just fair on debut before a spell but it was in a much stronger race and she can be an improver this time in.
